    "content": "<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n    <title>Big-O Notation Demo</title>\n    <style>\n        body {\n            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\n            margin: 20px;\n            padding: 20px;\n            border: 1px solid #ccc;\n            background-color: #f9f9f9;\n        }\n        h1 {\n            color: #333;\n        }\n        .code {\n            background-color: #eee;\n            padding: 10px;\n            border: 1px solid #ccc;\n            border-radius: 5px;\n            overflow-x: auto;\n        }\n        .button {\n            padding: 10px 15px;\n            background-color: #007BFF;\n            color: white;\n            border: none;\n            border-radius: 5px;\n            cursor: pointer;\n        }\n        .button:hover {\n            background-color: #0056b3;\n        }\n        .result {\n            margin-top: 20px;\n            font-weight: bold;\n        }\n    </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n\n<h1>Understanding Big-O Notation</h1>\n<p>Click the buttons below to see how different algorithms perform with increasing input sizes.</p>\n\n<button class=\"button\" onclick=\"testLinear()\">O(n) - Linear Time</button>\n<button class=\"button\" onclick=\"testQuadratic()\">O(n^2) - Quadratic Time</button>\n<button class=\"button\" onclick=\"testConstant()\">O(1) - Constant Time</button>\n\n<h2>Results</h2>\n<div id=\"result\" class=\"result\"></div>\n\n<script>\n    function testLinear() {\n        const n = 1000; // size of input\n        let sum = 0;\n        for (let i = 0; i < n; i++) {\n            sum += i; // Linear operation\n        }\n        document.getElementById('result').innerText = `O(n): Processed ${n} elements. Sum = ${sum}`;\n    }\n\n    function testQuadratic() {\n        const n = 100; // size of input\n        let count = 0;\n        for (let i = 0; i < n; i++) {\n            for (let j = 0; j < n; j++) {\n                count++; // Quadratic operation\n            }\n        }\n        document.getElementById('result').innerText = `O(n^2): Processed ${n} * ${n} elements. Count = ${count}`;\n    }\n\n    function testConstant() {\n        const n = 1000; // size of input\n        const result = 42; // Constant operation\n        document.getElementById('result').innerText = `O(1): Processed ${n} elements. Result = ${result}`;\n    }\n</script>\n\n</body>\n</html>"
